        "responses": {
          "values": [
            {
              "role": "system",
              "content": "You are a product hiring assistant."
            },
            {
              "content": "=JOB DESCRIPTION:\n{{$json.jd}}\n\nRESUME:\n{{$json.resume_text}}\n\nYou are an expert hiring analyst.\nRules:\n- If JD contains responsibilities, you MUST infer skills from them.\n- Do NOT leave jd_skills empty if JD is provided.\n- Convert responsibilities into skills.\n- Example:\n  \"conduct market research\" → \"market research\"\n  \"analyze data\" → \"data analysis\"\n- Always extract at least 5–15 skills from JD.\n- Do not hallucinate unrelated skills, but inference from actions is REQUIRED.\nSteps:\n\n1. Extract Job Description skills and categorize into:\n   - technical_skills\n   - tools\n   - soft_skills\n\n2. Extract Resume skills in the same categories.\n\n3. Identify skill_gaps:\n   - Skills present in JD but missing or weak in Resume\n   - Only include meaningful gaps (not trivial ones)\n\n4. Suggest improvements:\n   - Must be actionable and specific\n   - Focus on measurable improvements (projects, tools, experience)\n\n5. Generate exactly 5 interview_questions:\n   - 2 technical (based on JD)\n   - 2 gap-based (target missing skills)\n   - 1 resume deep-dive question\n\nOutput Requirements:\n- Output MUST be valid JSON\n- No markdown, no explanations, no extra text\n- All keys must always be present\n\nReturn JSON:\n\n{\n  \"jd_skills\": {\n    \"technical_skills\": [],\n    \"tools\": [],\n    \"soft_skills\": []\n  },\n  \"resume_skills\": {\n    \"technical_skills\": [],\n    \"tools\": [],\n    \"soft_skills\": []\n  },\n  \"skill_gaps\": [],\n  \"improvements\": [],\n  \"interview_questions\": []\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "builtInTools": {},
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.openAi",
      "typeVersion": 2.3,
      "position": [
        1280,
        -176
      ],
      "id": "b0d85a18-bdf3-408e-8507-09c61bde8d3d",
      "name": "Message a model",
      "credentials": {
        "openAiApi": {
          "id": "qaQvllYuWZWrlKmT",
          "name": "n8n free OpenAI API credits"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "mode": "runOnceForEachItem",
        "jsCode": "const raw = $json.output?.[0]?.content?.[0]?.text || \"\";\n\nconst clean = raw.replace(/```json|```/g, \"\").trim();\n\nlet parsed = {};\ntry {\n  parsed = JSON.parse(clean);\n} catch (e) {\n  return {\n    json: {\n      pageId: $json.pageId,\n      name: $json.name,\n      error: \"JSON parse failed\",\n      raw\n    }\n  };\n}\n\nconst safeArray = val => Array.isArray(val) ? val : [];\n\nconst jdSkills = [\n  ...safeArray(parsed.jd_skills?.technical_skills),\n  ...safeArray(parsed.jd_skills?.tools),\n  ...safeArray(parsed.jd_skills?.soft_skills)\n];\n\nconst resumeSkills = [\n  ...safeArray(parsed.resume_skills?.technical_skills),\n  ...safeArray(parsed.resume_skills?.tools),\n  ...safeArray(parsed.resume_skills?.soft_skills)\n];\n\nreturn {\n  json: {\n    pageId: $json.pageId,\n    name: $json.name,\n\n    jd_skills: jdSkills.join(\", \"),\n    resume_skills: resumeSkills.join(\", \"),\n    skill_gaps: safeArray(parsed.skill_gaps).join(\", \"),\n    improvements: safeArray(parsed.improvements).join(\"\\n\\n\"),\n    questions: safeArray(parsed.interview_questions).join(\"\\n\\n\")\n  }\n};"
      },
